    <section class="destination-section">
        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Monasteries of Meteora</h2>
        <p>Together, the famous monasteries of Meteora make up an incredible UNESCO world heritage site, which is also among Greece's most iconic and popular sights. The monasteries of Meteora are located just above the town of Kalabaka.</p>
        <p>The Meteora complex consists of six different monasteries built atop tall rock pillars with steep cliffs, with the most famous being the <strong>Great Meteor</strong>, the <strong>Monastery of the Holy Trinity</strong>, and the <strong>Monastery of Varlaam</strong>.</p>
        <p>The monasteries of Meteora were built between the 14th and 16th, and all six are definitely worth visiting, including the <strong>Monastery of St. Nicholas Anapavsa</strong>, <strong>Monastery of Rousanou</strong>, and the <strong>Monastery of St. Stephen</strong>.</p>
        <p>Be sure to also take in the various viewpoint from and between the monasteries, as the surrounding landscape and rock pillars are stunningly beautiful. Especially noteworthy are the views from the observation deck near the ruins of the <strong>Ypapanti Monastery</strong>, as well as the nearby <strong>Observation Deck</strong> between the Monasteries of Rousanou and the Holy Trinity.</p>
        <p>The monasteries and viewpoints in this itinerary are listed below in order beginning from the town of Kastraki, following along the winding road, ending at the Monastery of St. Stephen at the end of the road above Kalabaka.</p>
